struggle to pay for the rising
cost of living

23:47.226 --> 23:55.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
here on tiny wages. Until
recently, Ahmed
Kaju worked in the bakery. But
$10 a day didn't

23:55.467 --> 24:00.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pay the rent. He now feels he
must make a
desperate choice.

24:00.806 --> 24:06.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
"I want to go to Germany,
because they say
the living is good and that they
want to help

24:06.645 --> 24:12.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Syrians," he said. So, I
will go just
like everybody else, to Turkey
and from Turkey

24:13.052 --> 24:13.852 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to Greece.

24:13.952 --> 24:15.688 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
In a boat?

24:15.788 --> 24:20.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AHMED KAJU, Refugee (through
translator):
Yes, in a boat to Greece, and
from there,

24:20.225 --> 24:22.528 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we will continue with everybody
else.

24:22.628 --> 24:24.863 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: With your family?

24:24.963 --> 24:28.334 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AHMED KAJU (through translator):
With my family,
my son and my daughter.

24:28.434 --> 24:31.136 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: But it's very
dangerous.

24:31.236 --> 24:35.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AHMED KAJU (through translator):
But I'm dying
here. I might as well die there.
It's the

24:35.774 --> 24:39.478 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
same in the end. Let me die
trying.

24:39.578 --> 24:46.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: We traveled
across town to
the impoverished neighborhood of
Bourj el-Barajneh,

24:46.819 --> 24:51.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where we met another Syrian
refugee family
hoping to make it to Europe
soon.

24:52.091 --> 24:58.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jinan Jamal's husband survived
the dangerous
boat journey from Turkey four
months ago.

24:58.931 --> 25:04.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She stayed behind with their
three young boys.
Now in Germany, her husband is
trying to get

25:04.403 --> 25:10.909 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
asylum for Jinan and the
