going on.

46:04.228 --> 46:09.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, Michael Jordan was a
brilliant basketball
player, but he skipped steps to
get there.

46:09.200 --> 46:13.671 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And when it came time to
instruct people,
not great idea for a coach. The
same way maybe

46:13.771 --> 46:17.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
your kid plays the violin, the
best virtuoso
in the world is probably not the
best violin

46:18.075 --> 46:19.910 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
teacher.

46:20.011 --> 46:22.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we see in sports is that
like guys like
Gary Kubiak and Ron Rivera, who
they played,

46:22.113 --> 46:25.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they didn't pull these guys off
the street,
but they weren't at that top
echelon. They're

46:26.017 --> 46:28.452 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
actually better able to
articulate what's
going on.

46:28.552 --> 46:32.356 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And you
